text: Listen to ‘The Field’Policing and power in Minneapolis.
Listen to ‘Sway’ With Kara SwisherIn Opinion: Gavin Newsom’s trial by wildfire.

President Trump introduced Judge Barrett as his nominee in a Rose Garden ceremony, calling her “one of our nation’s most brilliant and gifted legal minds.”The nomination will ignite a partisan battle amid a volatile presidential campaign, drawing sharp lines on some of the country’s most divisive disputes.
Read the full transcript of Judge Amy Coney Barrett’s remarks.
If Judge Amy Coney Barrett is confirmed, the court would move firmly to the right, putting at risk the right to abortion established in Roe v. Wade.
Joe Biden and other Democrats will focus on the real-world impact she might have as a Supreme Court justice on health care and access to abortion.
He reveres custom and recognizes the courts’ essential role in shaping a policy agenda. Those dual instincts have perhaps never been in greater conflict.
Members of the Proud Boys pray before a rally in Portland, Ore., on Saturday. Mason Trinca for The New York Times

How a Pledge to Dismantle the Minneapolis Police CollapsedWhen City Council members promised to “end policing as we know it” after George Floyd’s killing, they became a case study in how such calls can falter.
Read how The Times’s visual investigation unit analyzes footage of police, protests and violence, frame by frame.

China Gives Unproven Covid-19 Vaccines to Thousands, With Risks UnknownDrug company workers, government officials and others have been injected. More will be soon, bewildering experts.
